dismissalText.commentary: Imrul Kayes c †Paine b Pattinson 93 (95b 10x4 2x6 121m) SR: 97.89

dismissalComment.html: Imrul Kayes has fallen after a brave fine knock. Siddons looks shocked.  It was a full delivery angling away from Kayes who goes for the off drive. He reaches out, away from his body and get a thin edge. The debutant James Pattinson gets his moment under the sun.

commentPreTextItems.html: AB: "I think it is the time to get a genuine test batsman like Justin  Langer as Bangladesh's coach."

commentTextItems.html: low full toss on the middle, driven past the bowler for couple of runs. Australia have won the series 3-0.

commentPostTextItems.html: Much better show from Bangladesh. This is their second highest score - they hit 296 against India - against Test-playing nations. Tamim gave the start, Kayes built on it and there were contributions from Nafees and Mahmudullah but Australia still win this by 66 runs.
Please wait for the quotes from the post-match ceremony

Man of the match is Hussey: "It was a great day. I really enjoyed it. It was a big chase for them but I thought they chased it well. I was in a bit earlier than lot of my innings; judging the conditions and get a move-on from there. It was a such a good batting pitch that we could get the momentum going. There wasn't much for the bowlers, not much spin, quite different from the first game."

Man of the series is Shane Watson: "After the second game and today to get 360, it was a quite a good platform. The guys were able to get the momentum going. It's been a lot of fun;; this is my first tour of Bangladesh and it was nice to have played as well as we have."

Shakib: "We batted really well. we executed our plans with the bat. We haven';t bowled well with the ball in the three games. It's a learning process and we will learn from it. Everytime you play a bigger team, you learn from them .. how they approached themselves when they batted and the areas where they bowled. Nafees came back into the team after a long time and scored consistently. Riaz and Kayes have performed well."

Clarke: "It was a good series. Outstanding effort from the boys. Ferguson, Paine were with us through the world-cup, were keen to get a game. Pattinson made his debut. Philosphy of captaincy? Keep winning! I am lucky that Ponting is in the team. As a young captain I need to keep learning. Watson is enjoying his batting and also doing the job with the ball. We hope he can continue with his purple patch."
That's it from us. Good bye and good luck.

commentTextItems.html: Crash! The bouncer and Riad unfurls a spanking pull shot to fine-leg boundary.
Wow! Whiplashed! He moved outside leg and lashed the full delivery over backward point
slower one, just outside off, Mahmudullah mistimes it back to the bowler
backs away to lift this to sweeper cover

commentPreTextItems.html: Harry: "Don't understand why mortaza did not come out and this shuvo sent ahead?" Puzzling indeed.

commentTextItems.html: just outside off stump, slashed away to third man for a single
another tame push to covers

length delivery around off, pushed out to short cover

flicks this full delivery to left of midwicket for a single

Paine goes diving to his right to stop the wide but can't get there in time. Wayward delivery
in the zone outside off stump, moves past the defensive prod and it wobbles as it reaches Paine who makes a mess of it. Posthumous swing!

dismissalComment.html: Watson is out. Will the entertainment end? The crowd roar in delight. It was a nice delivery, much slower through the air and Watson is beaten by the lack of pace. he went for the big slog sweep and missed it completely. The ball landed, winked at him and gently pegged back the off stump.

dismissalText.commentary: Ricky Ponting lbw b Abdur Razzak 47 (50b 7x4 1x6 70m) SR: 94

dismissalComment.html: Ponting is not happy but he has to go. It was the full delivery on the middle and Ponting went for the sweep and missed it completely. that looked pretty close unless of course the ball was turning away sharply.

dismissalText.commentary: Steven Smith c & b Sohrawordi Shuvo 5 (9b 1x4 0x6 12m) SR: 55.55

dismissalComment.html: Caught and bowled! He took two steps down the track and ended up chipping it back to the bowler. Greg Mathews murmurs on air, "What a wasted opportunity" Tame dismissal but the bowler has to be given credit for getting the ball to dip

dismissalText.commentary: Michael Clarke b Mashrafe Mortaza 47 (62b 2x4 0x6 90m) SR: 75.8

dismissalComment.html: Clatter! Mortaza has knocked out the off stump. The Batting Powerplay strikes. It was the full delivery,  just short of the blockhole, on the off stump line, Clarke shuffled across and went for the big across-the-line swing. Mistake. No wood on leather but the opposite.

dismissalText.commentary: Imrul Kayes c †Paine b Pattinson 93 (95b 10x4 2x6 121m) SR: 97.89

dismissalComment.html: Imrul Kayes has fallen after a brave fine knock. Siddons looks shocked.  It was a full delivery angling away from Kayes who goes for the off drive. He reaches out, away from his body and get a thin edge. The debutant James Pattinson gets his moment under the sun.

dismissalText.commentary: Shahriar Nafees c Watson b Johnson 60 (86b 4x4 0x6 118m) SR: 69.76

dismissalComment.html: Nafees is done by the slower one. A lovely change of pace and Nafees picked it up very late. He lunged out in the end and ended up stabbing it straight up in the air. Watson came in and took it around short-leg position. Australia tighten the screws.

dismissalText.commentary: Mahmudullah not out 68 (61b 5x4 2x6 90m) SR: 111.47
Shakib Al Hasan c Doherty b Watson 9 (11b 0x4 0x6 17m) SR: 81.81

dismissalComment.html: Pouched at short fine-leg! Shakib shuffles across the stumps and tries the paddle lap around the corner but doesn't get the elevation.

dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c Smith b Watson 1 (4b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: Spontaneous combustion. It was slightly short delivery and Mush plays a very weak pull. The ball lobs to midwicket. Double strike for Watto
